Titolo: NFL Street 2

Anno: 2004

Descrizione: NFL Street 2 is American football video game developed by EA Sports BIG and published by Electronic Arts. It was originally released for the PlayStation 2, GameCube and Xbox on December 22, 2004. It features then-New York Giants tight end Jeremy Shockey and rapper Xzibit on the cover. The game is compatible with Madden NFL 06, as players can import their Own The City players to it. The game's compatibility also extends to other EA games like Need for Speed: Underground 2, SSX 3, Madden NFL 2005, NCAA Football 2005, NFL Street, GoldenEye: Rogue Agent, NBA Live 2005, and NBA Street Vol. 2, where if players have these games on their memory cards (or hard drive in Xbox's case), they can earn 25,000 points in the game.It was later ported to the PlayStation Portable in 2005 under the name NFL Street 2 Unleashed.

Genere: Sports 

Valutazione: 76
